<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 03 at 9:07PM EST  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern
Scotland, Anson, southern Montgomery, Richmond and southeastern
Stanly Counties through 1015 PM EST...
At 907 PM EST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Unionville, or 9 miles northeast of Monroe, moving northeast at 65
mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Rockingham, Wadesboro, Hamlet, Ansonville, Hoffman, Polkton, Norwood,
Mount Gilead, Ellerbe and Dobbins Heights.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
